UNITED NATIONS _ The United States urged other U.N. members at

talks Sunday to impose broad economic and military sanctions on Iraq.
U.S. Ambassador Thomas R. Pickering told reporters after closed-door talks Sunday that the council discussed "the absolute necessity of moving ahead toward a broad resolution of sanctions."
In Kuwait, the Iraqi-installed provisional government, in a statement carried by the Iraqi News Agency, told other countries to refrain from taking "punishing measures" against it or Iraq.
In Aspen, Colo., British Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher renewed her call for the United Nations to apply a total economic embargo against Iraq unless it withdraws immediately from Kuwait.
